Description: Stela carved from limestone, showing in relief a funerary banquet with snake and horse head.
Curator's comments: Gardner lists this as well as another grave stela as having been ‘found last year’ but not within ‘the limits of the ancient city’ (Gardner 1888: 22).
Bibliographic references: Sculpture / Catalogue of Greek Sculpture in the British Museum (728)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (CC.06)
